<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="335" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,258,1471]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1302,1327]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to the Magellanic 
<taxonomicName box="[836,955,1302,1327]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Argeneuthria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="philippi">
<emphasis box="[836,955,1302,1327]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">A. philippi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the shell is more slender with a longer spire, larger siphonal canal and the spiral ornamentation is always well defined on the teleoconch. In addition, the protoconch of 
<taxonomicName box="[459,587,1375,1398]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Argeneuthria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="varicosa" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[459,587,1375,1398]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">A. varicosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[593,652,1375,1398]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is larger, more conical and with a smaller first whorl. The number and morphology of the spiral cords as well as of the protoconch and varices clearly distinguish the shell of 
<taxonomicName box="[1308,1436,1411,1435]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Argeneuthria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="varicosa">
<emphasis box="[1308,1436,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">A. varicosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[212,347,1446,1471]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Pareuthria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="venustula">
<emphasis box="[212,347,1446,1471]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">P. venustula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although they do show certain degree of similarity.
</paragraph>
